# Product Note: PSU-3000 Series Replacement

**Document ID:** {% $markdoc.frontmatter.id %}
**Published:** {% $markdoc.frontmatter.publishDate %}
**Effective:** {% $markdoc.frontmatter.effectiveDate %}

{% callout type="info" %}
**Product Transition Announcement**: The PSU-3000 series is being replaced by the new PSU-3000-X series, featuring enhanced performance, improved efficiency, and new capabilities.
{% /callout %}

## Summary

Effective **January 15, 2026**, the PSU-3000 series programmable power supplies will be replaced by the new PSU-3000-X series. This document outlines the transition timeline, product differences, migration guidance, and support for existing customers.

![PSU-3000-X Product Photo]({{ files.find(f => f.description.includes('product-photo')).cdnUrl }})

## Affected Products

The following products are being replaced:

| Model | Status | Last Order Date | Replacement Model |
|-------|--------|-----------------|-------------------|
| **PSU-3000** | Being replaced | 2026-01-15 | **PSU-3000-X** |
| **PSU-3000-LV** | Being replaced | 2026-01-15 | **PSU-3000-X-LV** |

## Replacement Products

### PSU-3000-X Series

The new PSU-3000-X series offers significant improvements:

**Key Enhancements:**
- **Higher efficiency**: >92% typical (vs. 88% in PSU-3000)
- **Lower noise**: <5mVrms output ripple (vs. 10mVrms)
- **Faster transient response**: <50μs (vs. 100μs)
- **Enhanced connectivity**:
  - Gigabit Ethernet (100Mbps in PSU-3000)
  - USB-C (USB-B in PSU-3000)
  - Optional Wi-Fi module
- **Improved user interface**: 4.3" color touchscreen (vs. 2.4" monochrome LCD)
- **Remote sensing**: Standard (optional in PSU-3000)
- **Programmable sequences**: 100 program slots (10 in PSU-3000)

**Maintained Capabilities:**
- Same output specifications (0-30V, 0-100A, 3000W)
- Compatible mounting (drop-in rack replacement)
- Same output connector types
- Backward compatible SCPI command set

For complete feature comparison, see the [comparison chart PDF]({{ files.find(f => f.description.includes('comparison')).cdnUrl }}).

