## Frequently Asked Questions

### General Questions

**Q: Do I need to replace my PSU-3000 units?**
A: No. Existing units will continue to be supported for 5 years from the last shipment date (until 2031-06-30).

**Q: Will my PSU-3000 firmware continue to be updated?**
A: Yes, firmware updates will be provided until 2028-06-30 (3 years from production end).

**Q: Can I still buy a PSU-3000?**
A: Yes, until the last order date of 2026-01-15 (or while supplies last).

### Technical Questions

**Q: Is PSU-3000-X electrically compatible with PSU-3000?**
A: Yes, same output specifications and connector types. Drop-in replacement for most applications.

**Q: Will my existing software work with PSU-3000-X?**
A: Yes, PSU-3000-X is backward compatible with PSU-3000 SCPI commands and drivers.

**Q: Can I mix PSU-3000 and PSU-3000-X in my rack?**
A: Yes, they can be operated side-by-side in the same rack or test system.

**Q: What's the main reason to upgrade?**
A: Improved efficiency (lower operating costs), enhanced connectivity (Ethernet/Wi-Fi), better user interface (touchscreen), and future-proofing.

### Pricing and Ordering

**Q: Is PSU-3000-X more expensive than PSU-3000?**
A: Initial pricing is approximately 15% higher, but early adopter and trade-in discounts are available.

**Q: Can I get volume pricing?**
A: Yes, contact sales@example.com for volume discounts (5+ units).

**Q: What if I have an existing quote for PSU-3000?**
A: Contact your sales representative to discuss options (honor existing quote or update to PSU-3000-X).

